        "sender_full_name": "Artie Khovanov",
        "timestamp": 1742387933
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Best source for that is probably the Abhyanar book <br>\nOh yeah also note that I don't know how to generalise from Puiseaux to Hahn series<br>\nOr even if the argument I gave above does generalise<br>\nIt probably does</p>",
        "id": 506717493,
        "sender_full_name": "Artie Khovanov",
        "timestamp": 1742388177
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To your list of criteria for being a RCF, you could add <br>\n(5) -1 is not a square and R(sqrt (-1)) is algebraically closed, <br>\nwhich will allow to use the theorem that over an ACF, the field of Hahn series for a divisible group is also algebraically closed.</p>",
        "id": 507375470,
        "sender_full_name": "Antoine Chambert-Loir",
        "timestamp": 1742594756
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh yeah you can do that as well, good idea! Although yeah you can also generalise the proof directly, as I did</p>",
